+//! **ML-DSA-87 verify FRONT: the sigDecode-z block feeds BOTH its consumers consistently —
+//! `z = sigDecode(σ)` → { `ẑ = NTT(z)` (arithmetic path, wire 13) AND `‖z‖∞ < γ1−β` (acceptance
+//! path, wire 17) } in ONE recursion tree.**
+//!
+//! `sigdecode_z_join` bound the decoded z to the forward NTT (the arithmetic consumer). But `Verify`
+//! ALSO feeds the SAME z to the norm-bound acceptance check (`‖z‖∞ < γ1−β`, `norm_bound_air.rs`,
+//! wire 17). If those two consumers could read DIFFERENT z's, a prover could pass the norm check
+//! with a small z while the matvec uses a forged large one. This example closes that: it surfaces
+//! the sigDecode output BOTH as the residue `z_q` (fed to the NTT) AND as the raw `t = γ1 − z` (fed
+//! to the norm bound), and binds each to its consumer in ONE outer proof — so the z that passes
+//! acceptance is provably the z the arithmetic uses.
+//!
+//! ```text
+//!                      ┌── Tie_F: z_q ── z ──forwardNTT──▶ ẑ        (Leg F, wire 13)
+//!   σ z-bytes ──BitUnpack──▶ (raw, z_q)
+//!   (Leg SD)               └── Tie_N: raw == t = γ1−z ──▶ ‖z‖∞<γ1−β  (Leg N, wire 17)
+//! ```
+//!
+//!   - **Leg SD — sigDecode z** (`SigDecodeZAir`, VERBATIM `sigdecode_z_air.rs`): now surfaces BOTH
+//!     `raw[0..8]` (= `t = γ1−z`) AND the residue `z_q[0..8]` = `(γ1−raw) mod q`. NG=4 groups/row → 8
+//!     coeffs. **16 pubs** (`raw ‖ z_q`).
+//!   - **Leg F — forward NTT** (`NttAir`, VERBATIM): `ẑ = NTT(z)`, z INPUT [0..8] / ẑ OUTPUT [8..16].
+//!   - **Leg N — norm bound** (`NormAir`, ported VERBATIM from `norm_bound_air.rs`): the FIPS-204
+//!     `‖z‖∞ < γ1−β` acceptance predicate — each coeff carried as `t = γ1−z`, checked `β < t < 2γ1−β`
+//!     via two 20-bit range slacks. 8 coeffs/row. Surfaces its `t[0..8]` INPUT.
+//!   - **Tie_F (SD↔F):** `Leg-SD z_q[k] == Leg-F z_in[k]`; **Tie_N (SD↔N):** `Leg-SD raw[k] == Leg-N t[k]`.
+//!
+//! ## Cases (all in one run)
+//!   1. HONEST (both consumers read the SAME decoded z): outer prove+verify SUCCEEDS.
+//!   2. NEG-REGROUP (tamper a coeff off its 20-bit grouping): Leg SD native verify REJECTS.
+//!   3. NEG-NORM (a z that violates ‖z‖∞ < γ1−β): Leg N native verify REJECTS.
+//!   4. NEG-TIE-F (NTT z ≠ sigDecode's z_q): Tie_F mismatch → REJECTS at prove.
+//!   5. NEG-TIE-N (norm t ≠ sigDecode's raw): Tie_N mismatch → REJECTS at prove.
+//!
+//! ```bash
+//! cargo run --release --example sigdecode_z_consumers_join
+//! ```
+
